data.value: Cataracts occur when the lens becomes less transparent due to changes or damage caused by oxidization, it usually appear on the lens as people grow older. Cataracts are fortunately treatable however it is still a serious condition that affects hundreds of thousands of people in the UK alone. Cataracts are usually not painful and symptoms include, Blurred vision lights may appear glaring or too bright and colors may appear faded
